{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611006","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611006"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:06:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:06:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16189"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16189","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16189"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.03,0.08,0.89,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8880"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115376"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8880","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8880"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16189"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97379"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2333"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5322"},{"type":"tags","id":"7001"},{"type":"tags","id":"7017"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10118"},{"type":"tags","id":"10640"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21142"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21145"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21401"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115376"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring breastfeeding, nipple stimulation activates sensory neurons that signal to the hypothalamus. This stimulates the release of a key hormone from the posterior pituitary that acts on the breast tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following hormones is released from the posterior pituitary to stimulate milk ejection during breastfeeding?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acetylcholine","Dopamine","Gonadotropin releasing hormone","Oxytocin","Serotonin"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOxytocin\u003C/strong\u003E is synthesized in the paraventricular and supraoptic nuclei of the hypothalamus and released from the posterior pituitary in response to nipple stimulation during breastfeeding. It travels through the bloodstream to act on myoepithelial cells surrounding the milk-producing alveoli, causing them to contract and eject milk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcetylcholine\u003C/strong\u003E is a neurotransmitter involved in parasympathetic signaling, not a posterior pituitary hormone. \u003Cstrong\u003EGonadotropin releasing hormone\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by the hypothalamus but acts on the anterior pituitary, not the breast. \u003Cstrong\u003EDopamine\u003C/strong\u003E actually inhibits prolactin release and thus reduces milk production. \u003Cstrong\u003ESerotonin\u003C/strong\u003E is a neurotransmitter not involved in milk ejection.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Oxytocin is released from the posterior pituitary in response to nipple stimulation during breastfeeding.","Oxytocin causes contraction of myoepithelial cells in the breast, leading to milk ejection.","The paraventricular and supraoptic nuclei of the hypothalamus produce oxytocin which is stored and released from the posterior pituitary."],"references":["Erickson EN, Carter CS, Emeis CL. Oxytocin, Vasopressin and Prolactin in New Breastfeeding Mothers: Relationship to Clinical Characteristics and Infant Weight Loss. J Hum Lact. 2020 Feb;36(1):136-145. doi: 10.1177/0890334419838225. Epub 2019 Apr 29. PMID: 31033381; PMCID: PMC9766886.","Uvn\u00e4s Moberg K, Ekstr\u00f6m-Bergstr\u00f6m A, Buckley S, Massarotti C, Pajalic Z, Luegmair K, Kotlowska A, Lengler L, Olza I, Grylka-Baeschlin S, Leahy-Warren P, Hadjigeorgiu E, Villarmea S, Dencker A. Maternal plasma levels of oxytocin during breastfeeding-A systematic review. PLoS One. 2020 Aug 5;15(8):e0235806. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0235806. PMID: 32756565; PMCID: PMC7406087.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97379"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16189"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97379","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97379"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T13:56:34+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T13:58:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8880"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115376"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"at